text:
Regulations on renaming of Pereyaslav-Khmelnitsky and a number of villages have been published

04 Nov 2019, 12:40


The parliamentary edition of the Voice of Ukraine published resolutions on the renaming of Pereyaslav-Khmelnitsky and several villages.

This is stated in the November 2 edition.
"The Verkhovna Rada decrees:
Rename Pereyaslav-Khmelnitsky city of Kyiv region to Pereyaslav city;
Rename the village Ostrovki of the Manevichi district of Volyn region to the village Ostrove;
Rename the village Rachki of Nemyriv district to the village Podilskoe;
Rename Borki village of Sokal district of Lviv region to Borki village;
Rename the village Mazarnya-Karanska Kamianka-Buzky district of Lviv region to the village Mazarnya-Karanskaya. "
Recall that in the town of Novgorod in the Donetsk region, which is subordinate to the Toretsk Civil Military Administration, part of the residents advocated the return of the historic name of New York.

